 Section 2(a) of the Kerala Esseential Articles Control (Temporary Powers) Act, 1961 defines "essential article" as meaning any article (not being an essential article as defined in Essential Commodities Act. 1955) which may be declared by the Government by a notification to be an essential article. Section 3 enables the State Government, if of the opinion that it is necessary or expedient so to do for maintaining or increasing the supplies of any essential article etc. to make certain notified orders. The Act was originally intended to be in force for five years but its life was extended by successive amendments.
 
